
/* Rohan works for a logistics company that delivers packages across multiple cities.
The delivery network is represented as a graph where:

Each city is represented as a vertex (node).
Each road between two cities is represented as an edge.
Each road has a travel time (weight).

Rohan needs to calculate the minimum travel time from the main warehouse city (source city) to all other cities.

Write a program to find the shortest travel time from the source city to every other city using Dijkstra’s Algorithm.

Input Format
The first line contains an integer V
→ the number of cities (vertices).
The second line contains an integer E
→ the number of roads (edges).
The next E lines each contain three integers:
u v w

Where:

u = source city
v = destination city
w = travel time between city u and city v
The last line contains an integer src
→ the source city (warehouse city).
Output Format

Print the minimum travel time from the source city to every other city in ascending order of city number.

If a city is unreachable from the source city, print:

INF

for that city.

Example Input
5
6
0 1 4
0 2 1
2 1 2
1 3 1
2 3 5
3 4 3
0
Example Output
City 0 : 0
City 1 : 3
City 2 : 1
City 3 : 4
City 4 : 7 */
CODE IS:- 
import java.util.*;
public class Graphwaysfind {
    static class Pair {
        int node, weight;

        Pair(int node, int weight) {
            this.node = node;
            this.weight = weight;
        }
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int V = sc.nextInt(); // number of cities
        int E = sc.nextInt(); // number of roads

        ArrayList<ArrayList<Pair>> graph = new ArrayList<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < V; i++) {
            graph.add(new ArrayList<>());
        }

        // Input edges
        for (int i = 0; i < E; i++) {

            int u = sc.nextInt();  // source city
            int v = sc.nextInt();  // destination city
            int w = sc.nextInt();  // travel time between u and v.

            graph.get(u).add(new Pair(v, w));
            graph.get(v).add(new Pair(u, w)); // undirected graph
        }

        int src = sc.nextInt();   // 0 is source point.

        // Dijkstra Algorithm
        PriorityQueue<Pair> pq =
                new PriorityQueue<>((a, b) -> a.weight - b.weight);

        int[] dist = new int[V];

        Arrays.fill(dist, Integer.MAX_VALUE);  // initially unreachable.

        dist[src] = 0;

        pq.add(new Pair(src, 0));

        while (!pq.isEmpty()) {

            Pair current = pq.poll();

            int u = current.node;

            for (Pair neighbor : graph.get(u)) {

                int v = neighbor.node;
                int weight = neighbor.weight;

                if (dist[u] + weight < dist[v]) {

                    dist[v] = dist[u] + weight;

                    pq.add(new Pair(v, dist[v]));
                }
            }
        }

        // Output
        for (int i = 0; i < V; i++) {

            if (dist[i] == Integer.MAX_VALUE) {
                System.out.println("City " + i + " : INF");
            } else {
                System.out.println("City " + i + " : " + dist[i]);
            }
        }
    }
}
